Students learn and practice folk dances, learn traditional variants and create individual variation on the basis of tradition.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course comprises following topics: Estonian traditional dances and regional dance styles, variation and tradition, creative approach to folk dances, analysis of audiovisual archive sources (Setu and Kihnu, dance club movement), finding one's own natural bearing and personal dancing style.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students become acquainted with different types of Estonian folk dances,their music, steps and figures (including variants) and acquire knowledge and abilities to teach folk dances.
